    • Constructor Detail

      • ApplicationCreatorExt

        public ApplicationCreatorExt(String token,
                     String displayName,
                     String version)
        Creates an instance of ApplicationCreatorExt containing mandatory information.

        The created Application will used the default layout and the default theme. If you want to set a specific layout/theme, use ApplicationCreatorExt(String, String, String, long, long) instead.

        Parameters:
        token - the Application token. The token will be part of application URL. It cannot be null or empty and should contain only alpha numeric characters and the following special characters '-', '.', '_' or '~'.
        displayName - the Application display name. It cannot be null or empty
        version - the Application version
        See Also:
        Application

        Creates an instance of ApplicationCreatorExt containing mandatory information and a specific layout.

        displayName - the Application display name. It cannot be null or empty
        version - the Application version
        layoutId - the identifier of the Page to be used as Application layout
        themeId -
